== Installation notes ==

=== Compilation speed ===

The CPU is rather slow so it may be worth avoiding some steps that make the installation unnecessarily time consuming.

==== Installing genkernel/genkernel-next ====

When you're not using systemd, you can choose between {{Package|sys-kernel/genkernel}} and {{Package|sys-kernel/genkernel-next}}. The former is often used with {{Package|sys-fs/lvm2}} that with the ''thin'' use flag depends on {{Package|sys-block/thin-provisioning-tools}} that depend on {{Package|dev-libs/boost}} which is extremely slow to build. On the other hand, {{Package|sys-kernel/genkernel}} (as of Feb 2015) pulls in that dependency unconditionally.

Therefore I recommend to avoid {{Package|sys-kernel/genkernel-next}} entirely and to build {{Package|sys-kernel/genkernel}} instead and build {{Package|sys-fs/lvm2}} without the ''thin'' use flag when booting from LVM.

{{RootCmd|euse -p sys-fs/lvm2 -D thin}}

{{Emerge|genkernel lvm2}}

==== Changing CFLAGS, bootstrapping compiler and rebuilding the system ====

Either avoid bootstrapping the compiler and rebuliding the system or assign two days to the task. In a fresh installation it's not much work for you but both bootstrapping and rebuilding takes a lot of time. You may want to chain the two actions to wait only once.

{{RootCmd|/usr/portage/scripts/bootstrap.sh && emerge --emptytree world}}

